# To display everything in <dir>, excluding hidden files:
ls <dir>

# To display everything in <dir>, including hidden files:
ls -a <dir>

# To display all files, along with the size (with unit suffixes) and timestamp
ls -lh <dir>

# To display files, sorted by size:
ls -S <dir>

# To display directories only:
ls -d */ <dir>

# To display directories only, include hidden:
ls -d .*/ */ <dir>

# To display all files sorted by changed date, most recent first:
ls -ltc 

# To display files sorted by create time:
ls -lt

# To display files in a single column:
ls -1

# To show ACLs (MacOS):
# see also `cheat chmod` for `/bin/chmod` options for ACLs
/bin/ls -le


# -h --human-readable -A --almost-all do not list . ..  
# -F, --classify append indicator (one of */=>@|) to entries  
# alias l='ls -CF'   -C     list entries by columns
# -1     list one file per line
# -S     sort by file size, largest first
# -s, --size  print the allocated size of each file, in blocks
# -c     with -lt: sort by, mod time
# -t     sort by time, newest first; see --time
# -r     reverse sort
# -R 	Recursive listing
# ls -lah` --group-directories-first
| `alias ls=eza -la` --color=always --group-directories-first         |               |
| `alias lt=eza -lT` --color=always --group-directories-first         |  Tree listing               |
| `alias l.=eza -la` --color=always --group-directories-first ../        |                 |
| `alias l..=eza -la` --color=always --group-directories-first ../../        |                 |
